WARRI – A group under the aegis of Conference for the Actual­isation of Human Rights (CAHR), has urged the Delta State government and leaders of the Nigerian Police Force to name police officer slain during the EndSARS protests as hero of the Nigeria Police Reforms 2020 in Delta State. CAHR also stressed that the family of the slain police officer should be compensat­ed with N30 million as was done by the governments of Lagos, Anambra, Rivers and other states. CAHR said this in a state­ment signed by the Nation­al adviser Comr. Edewor Egedegbe, and the National Secretary, Comr. Atiku Sun­day, on December 23,2020 in Warri. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! The statement said, “We write on behalf of the family of Late Cpl Stanley Etaga, an Urhobo-born Nigerian and a native Assah, Ewu, Ughelli South Local Government Area of Delta State. “It is our findings that the Cpl. Stanley Etaga who joined the police force on the 17th of October 2011 was promoted to the rank of Cor­poral in June 2016 and was promoted to the rank of a sergeant seven days after his murder. SHOCKING! DOCTORS ARE MESMERIZED BY THIS NATURAL PREMATURE EJACULATION AND SMALL SIZE SOLUTION GUARANTEED TO BULLDOZE YOUR WOMAN INTO SEXUAL SUBMISSION